subject: Add depex support in bios.xml parsing.
commitMessage:
Add depex support in bios.xml parsing.

Added logic to execute depex expression for every knob in bios.xml.
knob is added to BiosAttributeRegistry only if depex evaluation result
is TRUE.

Tested:
By giving GET Request to
'redfish/v1/Registries/BiosAttributeRegistry/BiosAttributeRegistry'.
Output sample showing few knobs added becuase depex evaluation result
was TRUE:

{
    "AttributeName": "AEPErrorInjEn",
    "CurrentValue": "0x00",
    "DefaultValue": "0x00",
    "DisplayName": "AEPErrorInjEn",
    "HelpText": "Enable/Disable PMem Error Injection",
    "MenuPath": "./",
    "ReadOnly": false,
    "Type": "String",
    "Value": [
        {
            "OneOf": "0x0"
        },
        {
            "OneOf": "0x1"
        }
    ]
}
{
    "AttributeName": "wrVrefCenter",
    "CurrentValue": "0x01",
    "DefaultValue": "0x01",
    "DisplayName": "wrVrefCenter",
    "HelpText": "Write Vref Centering Disable/Enable",
    "MenuPath": "./",
    "ReadOnly": false,
    "Type": "String",
    "Value": [
        {
            "OneOf": "0x0"
        },
        {
            "OneOf": "0x1"
        }
    ]
}

Following are few knobs rejected becuase depex evaluation
result was FALSE:

<knob  type="scalar" setupType="oneof" name="PfrProvision"
varstoreIndex="04" prompt="PFR Provision"
description="Selectable if PFR is not locked." size="1"
offset="0x0126"
depex="Sif( PfrSupported _EQU_ 0 ) _AND_ Gif( PfrLockStatus _EQU_ 1 OR
PfrProvisionStatus _EQU_ 1 )"
default="0x00" CurrentVal="0x00">
    <options>
        <option text="Disable" value="0x0"/>
        <option text="Enable" value="0x1"/>
    </options>
</knob>

<knob  type="scalar" setupType="oneof" name="SataHotPlugController0_0"
varstoreIndex="01" prompt="
Hot Plug" description="Designates this port as Hot Pluggable." size="1"
offset="0x0119"
depex="Sif( PchSata_0 _EQU_ 0 ) _AND_
Sif( SataExternalController0_0 _EQU_ 1 )" default="0x00"
CurrentVal="0x00">
    <options>
        <option text="Disabled" value="0x0"/>
        <option text="Enabled" value="0x1"/>
    </options>
</knob>

Signed-off-by: Arun Lal K M <arun.lal@intel.com>
Change-Id: Iff1ea01fb06200e21cc7f2a2e0fdfdff70376581

Attributes such as name, description, CurrentVal, default and options from knob is used to fill BiosBaseTableTypeEntry. You can look at BiosBaseTableTypeEntry baseTableEntry = std::make_tuple(...); in line number 653 for more clarity.

Nit : Can using stringstream be useful here ?

My use case is to get the next word, and not to split the string into words, And yes stringstream can be used but since evaluateExpression is a recursive function splitting the whole statement into words will, in most cases, be an unwanted step. 

The design of the recursive function evaluateExpression can be changed in such a way that it uses only stringstream and effectively, but that might take more changes.

same as above

Any reason for this non blocking call ?
generateAndSendAttributesData takes around 1 minute and 10 seconds to complete. And since ipmiOEMSetPayload is an ipmi call, we dont want to keep it blocked for that much time.

irrespective of whether generate attributes and send attributes was successful or filure, payloadStatus would be set to ipmi::PStatus::Valid, and also it might return success at line 581. Wouldn't that be incorrect ?

As you said irrespective of generateAndSendAttributesData status, we return success to ipmiOEMSetPayload function, if steps till generateBIOSXMLFile is success. This is inevitable as generateAndSendAttributesData is called in a thread. But on the question that if it is incorrect behavior, we can assume that if generateBIOSXMLFile is successful bios.xml and all other required information is passed from bios to bmc. And generateAndSendAttributesData is to populate this given information to dbus and in-turn enabling the data to be visible through redfish GET to redfish/v1/Registries/BiosAttributeRegistry/BiosAttributeRegistry.

what will happen if a case of clearing the attributes and then the execution of async_method_call is ended up in error state and returns from if(ec)? Just to make sure that the previous data is not lost when you are not able to execute the current function in place which fails.

The only time the function will be called is when bios boots up. And the call comes to this function from ipmi call ipmiOEMSetPayload. And for a retry to happen ipmiOEMSetPayload has to be called again. In that case we will again generate attributesData. So, in effect, we can clear attributesData if the dbus call is successful or not.
Done

This is return for the lambda function. It is put there so that "phosphor::logging::log<phosphor::logging::level::INFO>("sendAllAttributes: send all attributes - done");" is not called in case of error. 
Even if I return "false" it is not being used because the lambda function is the completion handler.

Code readability will be improved if we aren't hard coding and one header place to change any of the hard coding values should be good enough i think.

"org.freedesktop.DBus.Properties" is hard coded in all places that I checked. In intel-ipmi-oem code base. Hence it is kept like this to be consistent with rest of the code.

In doDepexCompute() it is common that some knobs will have a invalid depex, I have observed around 14 failure knobs and 16048 successful knobs from the bios.xml that I used for testing.
So we just log the errors and continue operation, instead of aborting the operation. 
getBaseTable() returns false when size is zero. In this case we need to still make the sendAllAttributes() call so that a redfish call to Registries/BiosAttributeRegistry/BiosAttributeRegistry will not return the old list.
